		}
		{
			dependencies: ["41BA52E902F54F5F"]
			description: [
				"Gregtech Energy can be a bit challenging at first. Here are some tips to help."
				""
				"1. Each voltage Tier increases EU/t by 4x. Example: LV is 32 EU/t, while MV is 128 EU/t."
				"2. Amperage correlates to how many machines can be powered. Example: If you have a 4A cable, that cable can supply whatever      voltage it is to 4 machines. "
				"3. If you supply more voltage than a machine can handle, it WILL explode."
				"4. Sending more amps into a cable than it can handle WILL burn the cable up. This can cause fires which WILL explode your machines."
				"5. Cable loss is pretty simple, each cable or wire has a specific cable loss stated in its tooltip. Example: A Tin cable has 1 EU loss     per block. So if you are supplying 32 EU/t into that cable, if you try to connect a machine 8 blocks from the power source, you    will only get 24 EU/t."
			]
			id: "6A3BA963C48CB2F9"
